50|$|Each {{player is}} dealt four cards that are placed, face down, {{in a row}} in front of him or her. Each player looks at the two {{outermost}} cards in their row, {{at the beginning of the}} game. Players may not look at any cards during the game except through the use of a Peek card. The remaining cards form a <b>draw</b> <b>pile,</b> and the top one is turned over to form a discard pile (if this card is a power card, it is shuffled back into the <b>draw</b> <b>pile</b> and a replacement is dealt).|$|R
